# Arkaul, Karaidelsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Arkaul (; , ArqawÄ±l) is a rural locality (a village) in Urgushevsky Selsoviet, Karaidelsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 4 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Arkaul is located  southwest of Karaidel (the district's administrative centre) by road.
